timeline.bodyText:
I don't think Retrofit has the built-in support passing multi-headers i.e. x-ms-meta-*.
One way I can think of handling this is by leveraging Retrofit Tag, so create a class to be tagged StorageMultiHeaders.
class StorageMultiHeaders {
   private String headerPrefix;
   private Map<String, String> headers;

   public StorageMultiHeaders(String headerPrefix, Map<String, String> headers) {
       this.headerPrefix = headerPrefix;
       this.headers = headers;
   }

   public String getHeaderPrefix() {..}
   public Map<String, String> getHeaders() {..}
}

@PUT("{containerName}")
Call<ResponseBody> createContainer(
  @Path("containerName") String containerName,
  @Query("timeout") Integer timeout,
  @Header("x-ms-meta-") Map<String, String> metadata,
  @Header("x-ms-blob-public-access") PublicAccessType access,
  @Header("x-ms-version") String version,
  @Header("x-ms-client-request-id") String requestId,
  @Query("restype") String restype,
  @Header("x-ms-default-encryption-scope") String defaultEncryptionScope,
  @Header("x-ms-deny-encryption-scope-override") Boolean encryptionScopeOverridePrevented, 
  @Tag StorageMultiHeaders multiHeaders);
then when we call the service method, use StorageMultiHeaders type.
StorageMultiHeaders multiHeaders = new StorageMultiHeaders("x-ms-meta-", metadata);
service.createContainer(..., multiHeaders);
and add an interceptor in the StorageBlobServiceImpl
this.service = serviceClientnewBuilder()
    .addInterceptor(new Interceptor() {
    @Override
    public okhttp3.Response intercept(Chain chain) throws IOException {
        StorageMultiHeaders multiHeaders
                = chain.request().tag(StorageMultiHeaders.class);
        if (multiHeaders != null) {
            Request.Builder requestBuilder = chain.request().newBuilder();
            Map<String, String> headers = multiHeaders.getHeaders();
            for (Map.Entry<String, String> entry : headers.entrySet()) {
                requestBuilder.addHeader(multiHeaders.getHeaderPrefix() + entry.getKey(), entry.getValue());
            }
            return chain.proceed(requestBuilder.build());
        } else {
            return chain.proceed(chain.request());
        }
    }
   })
    .getRetrofit().create(StorageBlobService.class);

